          "github-summary",
          "github-reference-repo-setup"
        ],
        "documentHtml": "<section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;box-sizing:border-box;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,252,245,0.99), rgba(255,248,235,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(146,64,14,0.16);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(180,83,9,0.10);gap:14px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;min-width:0;\"><div style=\"font:700 11px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#b45309;\">Title</div><div style=\"font:700 28px/1.12 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;word-break:break-word;\">GitHub</div></div><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;flex-shrink:0;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(180,83,9,0.1);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.04em;\">headline</span><span style=\"font:600 10px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#9a3412;opacity:0.72;\">active</span></div></div><div style=\"height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(245,158,11,0.45), rgba(245,158,11,0));\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.65 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#4b5563;\">How GitHub works in Twilite today: connector-backed repository and PR context, local git and gh for checkout and Actions gaps, and explicit publish workflows.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Introduction</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Twilite's GitHub integration is currently hybrid. Use the GitHub app/plugin for repository, issue, pull request, comment, label, reaction, and PR creation workflows. Use local git and gh when the connector does not cover the job well, especially for branch state, commit and push, current-branch PR discovery, and GitHub Actions log inspection.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Connector first, local tools where needed</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The connector is preferred for structured repository, issue, pull request, patch, comment, label, reaction, and PR-creation flows. Local git and gh remain necessary for checkout-aware work: branch creation, staging, commit and push, auth checks, current-branch PR discovery, and Actions logs. Keep connector state and local checkout context aligned.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">What you can do today</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The current GitHub surface covers repository orientation, PR and issue triage, PR metadata summaries, patch inspection, comment and review follow-up, failing GitHub Actions investigation, and publish flow from local changes to a draft pull request. These are real, differentiated workflows, not one generic button.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">How to use the GitHub integration</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Start by naming the intent clearly. Use the umbrella GitHub path for general repo, PR, or issue help. Route to the specialist comment, CI, or publish workflows as soon as the task becomes specific. If the request is about the current branch or current PR, resolve local git context instead of pretending the connector alone knows branch state.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Boundaries and current status</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Do not imply that Actions logs come from the connector alone. Use gh for GitHub Actions checks and logs. Publish flow still requires local branch awareness and explicit scope confirmation before staging, commit, push, and draft PR creation. Beta readiness still tracks GitHub App migration as unfinished, so this graph describes the working hybrid model, not the final end state.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">GitHub App Migration</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(124,58,237,0.14);color:#5b21b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Reference</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #8b5cf6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Archived task graph for the larger GitHub App migration front.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Locator: /tasks/archive/github-app/root.node</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Beta Readiness Board</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(124,58,237,0.14);color:#5b21b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Reference</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #8b5cf6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The beta board still treats GitHub App migration as an open front.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Locator: /tasks/beta-readiness/root.node</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Working note</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(245,158,11,0.16);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Annotation</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">This graph is intentionally about the working integration. It should not promise a fully unified GitHub surface until the migration front actually lands.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Anchor: boundaries • Author: Michael</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Summary</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(219,39,119,0.14);color:#9d174d;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Summary</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #db2777, #f472b6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">GitHub in Twilite is currently a hybrid workflow: connector-backed repository and pull-request context, local git and gh for checkout-aware work and Actions gaps, and explicit publish flow for commits, pushes, and draft PRs.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Scope: GitHub root</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Initial GitHub Repo Setup</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(124,58,237,0.14);color:#5b21b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Reference</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #8b5cf6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Active task graph for defining the first root/public/private repo structure and browser path model.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Locator: /tasks/github-integration/initial-repo-setup/root.node</div></div></section>",
        "summarySource": "node-updater",
        "updatedAt": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z",
        "svg": "<svg viewBox=\"0 0 220 160\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\"><rect x=\"24\" y=\"18\" width=\"172\" height=\"124\" rx=\"18\" fill=\"#fffdfa\" stroke=\"#0f172a\" stroke-width=\"5\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"38\" width=\"82\" height=\"14\" rx=\"7\" fill=\"#111827\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"68\" width=\"136\" height=\"16\" rx=\"8\" fill=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke=\"#111827\" stroke-width=\"3\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"96\" width=\"120\" height=\"12\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#dbeafe\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"118\" width=\"94\" height=\"12\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#e2e8f0\"/></svg>",
        "_classBinding": {
