      "data": {
        "title": "Introduction",
        "summary": "Twilite's current GitHub integration is built around explicit document identity. A graph can be opened at a `github://...` address, the toolbar can show the active document and save target separately, and the save panel can surface installation-scoped repo visibility instead of pretending local folders are GitHub authority.",
