      "width": 430,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Boundaries and current status",
        "summary": "Twilite can now classify GitHub destinations as `Writable`, `Accessible`, or `Blocked`, but only `Blocked` is a hard denial. `Accessible` means the installation can reach the repo even if Twilite cannot fully predict the final write outcome. Direct commits are still not a full substitute for local checkout-aware workflows such as branching, PR preparation, or Actions investigation.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "boundaries",
        "status": "active",
